

sourcing setup.bash, it runs script and copies env vars that setup.bash uses in its own enviroment, to the source calling shell enviroment





package.xml file containing meta information about the package

CMakeLists.txt file that describes how to build the code within the package


colcon build, build all the packages in the workspace



make ros2 run excecutable from a new node:
in setup.py entry_points


rosdep will check for package.xml files in its path or for a specific package and find the rosdep keys stored within.
rosdep check --from-paths src --ignore-src

show msg
ros2 interface package serial_motor_msgs
ros2 interface show serial_motor_msgs/msg/MotorVels

pass arguments
ros2 run package exe_name --ros-args -p param_name:=param_value


